The dividend income is not the substantial income of the shareholders. Taking the cash dividend as an example, the stock will directly deduct the stock price after the removal.
Just take a part of the money that was originally reflected in the stock price, unless you fill in the interest completely, there is no money at all. Request for investors
Take the "income" without actual profit to declare comprehensive income tax, and the dividend deduction rate can only be halved. It is unreasonable, and
Stock removal may not be able to fill in interest, and people who are unfortunately sticked are more peeling.
The policy should be abolished and restored the full deduction of the past, so as to benefit many retirement or petty bourgeoisies that rely on the living dividends.
 Can also encourage investors to invest in long -term

In Taiwan's society and even the world, the issue of calling platforms (Uber, etc.) on the Internet is highly different. Before taking office, Minister of Communications He Chendan also believed: "Uber problem is the real challenge. "." He said: This can no longer be resolved by a single decree. It is also necessary to consider consumer expectations. It is also praised by the media as "the Minister of Communications who wants to deal with the Uber problem." However, after Minister He Chendan took office, the only prescription of the Ministry of Communications was to cooperate with Liudu Police forces to launch an unprecedented central and local joint audit for Uber.
 
President Tsai Ing -wen shouted "the most communicated government in history" before he was elected, and emphasized that the people's expectations were "solving the problem." The government, which can be communicated, has been revised last year to complete the "White Paper on the Internet Policy" last year, and listed the "adjustment of sharing economic legal systems" as one of the action plans for promoting relevant policies and participating in public affairs. A few days ago, the "concept of the planning system planning system planning system planning system", one of the new and old governments' transfer projects, and also stated that when formulating control measures, it should be widely included in public opinions to reduce future derivative disputes and avoid costs and regulations adjust costs.
 
In response to the legitimacy of these platforms, the Ministry of Communications originally claimed that "⋯ Since such owners are not engaged in the car transportation business stipulated in the highway law. "Whether the dispute involves other government authorities of the government authority, please ask the relevant competent authorities to assist in clarifying." There was no investigation report. Then on the grounds of "the current regulations are not clear, in order to avoid disputes", it is self -corrected to apply for approval and business measures for the taxi passenger service industry, and the platform is determined that the platform is illegal. Later, the benchmark table of the illegal business penalty of the self -use vehicle was fired, and the driving was aggravated. The common characteristics of the above situation are decision -making opaque, not communicating with various circles, and not incorporated into public opinions.
 
In fact, the Ministry of Transport of the New and Old Government has always lacked open decision -making, and often stands on the opposite side. After adjusting the communication platform for the purpose of consensus consensus, the solicitation and consultation meeting of fireworks -like opinions, it has been nearly nine months. And the final case. However, since the platform and other platforms such as Uber have entered Taiwan, the laws and regulations are unknown. In the closed -door meeting of the Ministry of Communications or in private discussions, there are also many experts and scholars of all parties advocating to adjust the regulations to respond to innovation. Common opinions at the stage. In other words, what the Ministry of Communications does is to do without social consensus and high controversy.
 
In order to substantly resolve the dispute, the specific suggestions are as follows:

The relevant consulting meeting of the Ministry of Communications in the past, and clarify the relationship between its decision -making and the Ministry of Communications;
Carry out an empirical investigation and research on the online call platform, and confirm that it affects the impact of public welfare and traffic safety;
Put forward the national sharing economic strategy, implement the impact assessment of control, and develop whether to regulate and how to control it;
The results of the collection and consulting meeting of the opinions were proposed to the online call platform and the regulations of the taxi industry to adjust the discussion case, and incorporated the user as a interesting person to enter the subsequent discussions and other stages;
Suspension lawsuits and banning, but if necessary, continue to search for evidence on the actor.

The White House of the United States was signed and promulgated by the president in 2016/12/14. The U.S. Congress discussed only one and a half years. The two houses of the two houses immediately passed the legislation of PMIAA (Program Management Improvement Accountability Act) "The government called it called it. Plan) Act of Management Improvement "(31 U.S. C. §1550). The bill was agreed with Congress and White House to establish a mechanism for establishing a "systemic management standard" (PMO, the concept of the project management office), requiring federal government agencies to abide by the standards of planning, implementation and evaluation of project management, and improve the implementation of the executive performance performance performance To establish a model of "responsibility" of modern government agencies. 
The PMIAA Act is due to the two major policies, which is time -consuming and spending huge sums of money, but it cannot reach the project and cancel, cancel or even suspend the project. (About NT $ 243.5 billion) Budget, its management defects: unknown categories, long periods, etc., so that the people's taxes are put into water. 
Looking at the performance and current situation of Taiwan's past policies and large -scale plans, such as in recent years: Taoyuan Airport MRT, Taoyuan International Airport flooding, Golden Gate Bridge Project, Taichung Express Bus (BRT), or Nuclear Four stop work ... and so on. Return to fundamental discussions on the management standards and unified standards of national planning. In fact, administrative agencies at all levels still follow the rules of experience. Observed with the current regulations and systems, or the "Government Internal Control System" in the planning, or the "Supervision and Audit System" after implementation, but the national -level policies and implementation standards for large -scale plans have not yet been See you. 
Therefore, please formulate national plan management standards, so that when government agencies implement any plan, all sections of the initial, planning, execution, control and end of the plan are national -level policies. The implementation criteria are used as the standard of follow. 
In the central administrative system, the existing national standard CNS 21500 "Project Management Guidelines" and the International Standard ISO 21504 "Plan Management Guidelines" (currently drafted by the Standard Inspection Bureau), which is "Plan Management Policy Committee":
1. Formulate the basic standards for planning management policies, and establish a systematic management policy and implementation standards for the establishment of a systematic (including the establishment of the plan, starting, planning, implementation, control, and ending);
2. The plan for reviewing the review of the Supervisory Institute or the Audit Department is lacking, and proposes to improve suggestions and guidelines;
3. Hear the proposals of various units, and consolidate the information of each plan to supervise and manage the implementation process;
Fourth, become the main forum platform for cross -machine customs and improve its planning management, and become an experience learning and knowledge management platform for the relevant projects of the state government in the future;
5. Formulate the manager's manpower development strategy (function, professional, career, career) of the central administrative organ to maintain the function of sustainable operation. (It is recommended to consult "Personnel Administration Office of the Executive Yuan")
